_raw.rds` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: mk_raw.rds under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_G0k6LpYNGpJkgtevnF3B6zXF", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R packages, specifically `methylKit` for methylation data processing.\\n2. Use the `methRead` function from `methylKit` to read the three bismark coverage files located in the `input/` directory. Set the parameters as specified: `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`, `mincov=4`, `treatment=c(0, 0, 0)`, and `assembly='mock_v1'`.\\n3. Save the resulting `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using the `saveRDS` function.\\n4. Verify that the file `output/mk_raw.rds` has been created successfully.\\n5. Submit the task as complete if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `methylkit_load`\n\n# Real R-task: methylkit_load\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `fritjoflammers-snakemake-methylanalysis-finish` (family: `methylation`, stage: `early`, difficulty: `1`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline sco