\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/mk_raw.rds` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_G0k6LpYNGpJkgtevnF3B6zXF", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R packages, specifically `methylKit` for methylation data processing.\\n2. Use the `methRead` function from `methylKit` to read the three bismark coverage files located in the `input/` directory. Set the parameters as specified: `pipeline='bismarkCoverage'`, `mincov=4`, `treatment=c(0, 0, 0)`, and `assembly='mock_v1'`.\\n3. Save the resulting `methylRawList` object to `output/mk_raw.rds` using the `saveRDS` function.\\n4. Verify that the file `output/mk_raw.rds` has been created successfully.\\n5. Submit the task as complete if the file exists.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (564 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_G0k6LpYNGpJkgtevnF3B6zXF"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_O87ut3qYxHz2zpIV9cUwrCU4", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file paths\\nfiles <- list('input/sampleA.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleB.bismark.cov', 'input/sampleC.bismark.cov')\\n\\n# Load the data\\nmethyl_data <- methRead(\\n  location = files,\\n  sample.id = c('sampleA', 'sampleB', 'sampleC'),\\n  assembly = 'mock_v1',\\n  pipeline = 'bismarkCoverage',\\n  treatment = c(0, 0, 0),\\n  mincov = 4\\n)\\n\\n# Save the methylRawList object\\nsaveRDS(methyl_data, 'output/mk_raw.rds')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nLoading required package: GenomicRanges\nLoading required package: stats4\nLoading required package: BiocGenerics\nLoading required package: generics\n\nAttaching package: \u2018generics\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked